Solution:

Method 1: Using Subquery

SELECT MAX(salary) AS second_highest_salary
FROM employee
WHERE salary < (
    SELECT MAX(salary)
    FROM employee
);

Method 2: Using CTE

Alternatively, you can utilize a CTE instead of a subquery.

WITH highest_salary_cte AS (
  SELECT MAX(salary) AS highest_salary
  FROM employee
)

SELECT MAX(salary) AS second_highest_salary
FROM employee
WHERE salary < (
    SELECT highest_salary
    FROM highest_salary_cte
);

Method 3: Using Window Functions

SELECT salary
  FROM (SELECT *, 
        DENSE_RANK() OVER(ORDER BY SALARY DESC) AS d_rnk 
         FROM employee) t 
 WHERE d_rnk = 2;
